<font color="#808080">(CREAKING)</font>

22
00:01:42,102 --> 00:01:44,343
<i>"U?"</i>

23
00:01:51,244 --> 00:01:54,817
we never colored even one
of our paper flowers yellow.

24
00:02:29,749 --> 00:02:31,353
Give them back,
Christopher.

25
00:02:31,417 --> 00:02:33,761
Not until you quit
pounding on my wall, you freak.

26
00:02:33,820 --> 00:02:35,822
<font color="#808080">(TWINS GIGGLING)</font>

27
00:02:35,889 --> 00:02:37,732
Hey. What do you kids
think you're doing?

28
00:02:39,526 --> 00:02:40,869
I don't even get a hug?

29
00:02:40,927 --> 00:02:41,927
- <font color="#808080">(LAUGHTER)</font>
- Dad!

30
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:43,300
Daddy!

31
00:02:43,363 --> 00:02:47,175
Oh! I missed you all
so much!

32
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:48,838
<font color="#804040">TWINS</font>:
What did you bring us?

33
00:02:50,770 --> 00:02:52,443
For you, son.

34
00:02:52,472 --> 00:02:53,472
Thank you.

35
00:02:56,209 --> 00:02:58,416
Did you
forget about me?

36
00:03:02,715 --> 00:03:04,251
I could never
forget about you.

37
00:03:06,686 --> 00:03:08,393
It's so beautiful.

38
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:35,853
<font color="#808080">(KIDS LAUGHING AND GIGGLING)</font>

39
00:03:39,285 --> 00:03:40,787
Oh! I got you!

40
00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:43,394
<font color="#808080">(LAUGHTER)</font>

41
00:03:43,456 --> 00:03:45,959
Oh!

42
00:03:46,226 --> 00:03:48,832
<font color="#808080">(ALL CHUCKLING)</font>

43
00:03:49,762 --> 00:03:51,264
I wish you never
had to go away...

44
00:03:51,331 --> 00:03:52,639
For work again.

45
00:03:52,966 --> 00:03:54,377
Promise me you won't.

46
00:03:54,434 --> 00:03:55,674
I hate to break up the party...

47
00:03:55,702 --> 00:03:57,704
But dinner's almost ready,
and I made your favorite...

48
00:03:57,804 --> 00:03:59,249
Homemade apple pie.

49
00:03:59,272 --> 00:04:00,945
Corrine,
you shouldn't have.

50
00:04:01,007 --> 00:04:03,248
She didn't.

51
00:04:03,309 --> 00:04:05,289
You forgot to
take off the bakery label.

52
00:04:05,345 --> 00:04:09,316
Ugh. Cathy! Could never
get anything past you, huh?

53
00:04:09,382 --> 00:04:10,383
Yeah, mom.

54
00:04:10,450 --> 00:04:11,019
What's going on?

55
00:04:11,284 --> 00:04:13,787
I mean, you're wearing
a new dress and perfume.

56
00:04:13,853 --> 00:04:16,390
Well, the wife
of a vice-president...

57
00:04:16,456 --> 00:04:18,333
Can't wear
just any old thing.

58
00:04:18,591 --> 00:04:21,572
I was going to wait
until it was 100% official...

59
00:04:21,628 --> 00:04:23,335
But I got promoted...

60
00:04:23,396 --> 00:04:26,741
And I'm now the head of sales
of the entire east coast.

61
00:04:26,799 --> 00:04:28,005
That's great!

62
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:28,973
<font color="#804040">DAD</font>:
Thank you.

63
00:04:29,035 --> 00:04:30,412
<font color="#804040">CORRINE</font>:
He got promoted!

64
00:04:32,005 --> 00:04:34,383
He's so smart, that's why.

65
00:04:36,509 --> 00:04:38,989
<font color="#808080">(SNIFFLING)</font>

66
00:04:39,045 --> 00:04:41,582
<font color="#808080">(KNOCKING)</font>

67
00:04:43,716 --> 00:04:46,424
Nobody's here.

68
00:04:48,388 --> 00:04:50,299
Cathy...

69
00:04:50,356 --> 00:04:51,858
Hey.

70
00:04:54,460 --> 00:04:55,768
<font color="#808080">(SIGHS SOFTLY)</font>

71
00:04:55,828 --> 00:04:58,434
This is a big
opportunity for me.

72
00:04:58,464 --> 00:05:00,000
For all of us.

73
00:05:00,066 --> 00:05:03,070
I know what's
going to happen.

74
00:05:03,336 --> 00:05:05,441
You'll be away
all the time.

75
00:05:05,471 --> 00:05:06,848
Mom will be busy
with the twins.

76
00:05:06,906 --> 00:05:10,615
Christopher will act like
he's the man of the house.

77
00:05:10,677 --> 00:05:13,419
<font color="#808080">(SIGHING)</font>
I'll be totally forgotten.

78
00:05:13,913 --> 00:05:15,449
Can I tell you a secret?

79
00:05:16,482 --> 00:05:17,825
I bought this...

80
00:05:17,884 --> 00:05:19,625
On my last trip...

81
00:05:19,686 --> 00:05:21,723
And it's more money
than I should have spent...

82
00:05:21,754 --> 00:05:24,064
But the moment
I saw it...

83
00:05:24,324 --> 00:05:26,668
I knew you
had to have it.

84
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:35,373
<font color="#808080">(DAD CHUCKLES SOFTLY)</font>

85
00:05:36,469 --> 00:05:37,641
So, when I'm traveling...

86
00:05:37,704 --> 00:05:39,479
I need you
to be strong.

87
00:05:39,539 --> 00:05:41,712
Can you do that for me?

88
00:05:49,582 --> 00:05:51,425
Mommy!
Cathy's hurting me!

89
00:05:51,484 --> 00:05:52,656
It wouldn't hurt so much...

90
00:05:52,719 --> 00:05:54,562
If you'd sit still
for five seconds.

91
00:05:54,620 --> 00:05:55,064
Girls, please.

92
00:05:55,121 --> 00:05:56,691
Your dad's going to be home
in less than two hours.

93
00:05:56,756 --> 00:05:58,633
I need to ice the cake,
chill the champagne...

94
00:05:58,658 --> 00:05:59,659
where are your brothers?

95
00:05:59,726 --> 00:06:01,603
Why do I have to
wear a tie'?

96
00:06:01,661 --> 00:06:03,106
'Cause we're
the "dresden dolls."

97
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:05,070
I don't want
to be a doll.

98
00:06:05,131 --> 00:06:06,701
It's just a saying,
darling.

99
00:06:06,766 --> 00:06:09,042
Because the neighbors
think we look so perfect.

100
00:06:09,102 --> 00:06:11,514
<font color="#808080">(CHUCKLES)</font>
We are perfect.

101
00:06:14,607 --> 00:06:17,144
<font color="#808080">(MUSIC PLAYS ON THE STEREO, PEOPLE CHATTER)</font>

102
00:06:19,145 --> 00:06:21,648
<i>"U?"</i>

103
00:06:25,017 --> 00:06:26,792
why isn't
he here yet?

104
00:06:26,853 --> 00:06:28,662
He's probably just
stuck in traffic.

105
00:06:28,721 --> 00:06:30,667
When are we going
to eat the cake?

106
00:06:30,723 --> 00:06:31,599
I want it now!

107
00:06:31,657 --> 00:06:33,466
Can I take off
my tie, please?

108
00:06:33,526 --> 00:06:34,834
Just be patient,
darlings, okay?

109
00:06:34,894 --> 00:06:36,567
I'm going to go
freshen the ice.

110
00:06:36,629 --> 00:06:38,438
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

111
00:06:38,498 --> 00:06:40,500
<font color="#808080">(CAR DOOR SHUTS)</font>
I hear someone in the driveway.

112
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:42,045
<font color="#808080">(EXCITED MURMURING AND BUSTLING)</font>

113
00:06:44,771 --> 00:06:47,945
<font color="#808080">(DOOR CREAKS OPEN)</font>

114
00:06:47,974 --> 00:06:49,954
<font color="#808080">(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)</font>

115
00:06:53,713 --> 00:06:55,124
Mrs. dollanganger?

116
00:06:55,648 --> 00:06:57,924
I'm sorry, but, um...

117
00:06:58,818 --> 00:07:01,094
There's been an accident.

118
00:07:30,082 --> 00:07:31,993
Mama?

119
00:07:35,054 --> 00:07:36,590
Mom?

120
00:07:50,937 --> 00:07:53,474
All right, guys,
five more minutes.

121
00:07:53,506 --> 00:07:55,144
Is daddy
coming home tonight?

122
00:07:59,212 --> 00:08:01,783
No.

123
00:08:02,548 --> 00:08:05,028
Remember? We told you.

124
00:08:05,852 --> 00:08:07,160
He died.

125
00:08:09,789 --> 00:08:12,827
Sometimes,
when I really miss him...

126
00:08:12,892 --> 00:08:14,701
I just pretend
he's on a business trip...

127
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:16,762
And that he'll
be back any day.

128
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:22,839
You guys wash up for dinner.

129
00:08:27,039 --> 00:08:28,712
<font color="#808080">(FOOTSTEPS)</font>

130
00:08:28,774 --> 00:08:29,775
<i><font color="#808080">(SIGHS)</font></i>

131
00:08:32,144 --> 00:08:34,784
Mom, the twins want you
to read them a story.

132
00:08:34,847 --> 00:08:35,951
Is that the mail?

133
00:08:39,752 --> 00:08:40,958
Madame pomfrey says...

134
00:08:41,020 --> 00:08:42,727
I can't stay
in ballet class...

135
00:08:42,788 --> 00:08:44,961
Unless we pay
for last month.

136
00:08:47,226 --> 00:08:49,536
Are we going to be
okay without dad?

137
00:08:49,562 --> 00:08:51,269
I'm doing
the best I can.

138
00:08:51,531 --> 00:08:52,976
It's not easy
for a woman to get a job...

139
00:08:53,032 --> 00:08:55,273
And to support four kids
on her own.

140
00:08:55,535 --> 00:08:57,640
Look at me,
I'm an ornament.

141
00:08:57,703 --> 00:08:59,103
The only thing
I was ever good at...

142
00:08:59,105 --> 00:09:00,105
Was being pretty.

143
00:09:05,177 --> 00:09:06,952
You know...

144
00:09:07,013 --> 00:09:08,185
You're lucky.

145
00:09:08,247 --> 00:09:10,625
You had a dad that
thought you were special.

146
00:09:10,683 --> 00:09:12,219
Because I'm just like you.

147
00:09:12,285 --> 00:09:13,855
Well, in looks, maybe...

148
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:16,833
But you're more aggressive
and determined.

149
00:09:16,889 --> 00:09:18,732
You're just like his mother...

150
00:09:18,791 --> 00:09:20,702
And he loved
his mother.

151
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:22,831
Doesn't everyone
love their mother?

152
00:09:22,895 --> 00:09:25,239
Some mothers
are impossible to love.

153
00:09:25,264 --> 00:09:27,175
They don't act like
mothers at all.

154
00:09:30,703 --> 00:09:32,683
Have Christopher read
the twins a story...

155
00:09:32,738 --> 00:09:34,649
And put this in
the mailbox for tomorrow.

156
00:09:34,874 --> 00:09:36,751
Another one? But you
already sent a couple.

157
00:09:36,809 --> 00:09:38,686
It's late.
You should finish your homework.

158
00:09:57,930 --> 00:10:01,343
Cathy, Christopher!
Come inside, now.

159
00:10:02,835 --> 00:10:04,872
You know
all those letters I sent?

160
00:10:04,937 --> 00:10:07,349
Well, I finally got a response.

161
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:09,052
It's all working out
as I'd hoped.

162
00:10:09,108 --> 00:10:10,815
We can go live with
your grandmother...

163
00:10:10,876 --> 00:10:11,876
In Virginia.

164
00:10:11,877 --> 00:10:13,185
What grandmother?

165
00:10:13,245 --> 00:10:14,245
You and dad said...

166
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:15,850
That we never
had any family.

167
00:10:15,915 --> 00:10:17,952
Well...
It's complicated.

168
00:10:18,017 --> 00:10:19,963
My parents and I,
we didn't see eye-to-eye...

169
00:10:20,019 --> 00:10:22,898
So we thought it was best
to keep our distance...

170
00:10:22,922 --> 00:10:24,959
But with your father gone...

171
00:10:25,024 --> 00:10:26,833
This is our best hope
for now.

172
00:10:26,892 --> 00:10:28,371
What about school?

173
00:10:28,628 --> 00:10:29,902
And all
of our friends?

174
00:10:29,929 --> 00:10:31,374
And my ballet classes?

175
00:10:31,631 --> 00:10:34,202
You two are old enough
to understand...

176
00:10:34,266 --> 00:10:36,371
To help your mother
out of a desperate situation.

177
00:10:36,636 --> 00:10:38,240
But we still
have the house...

178
00:10:38,304 --> 00:10:39,977
And I can get
a part-time job...

179
00:10:40,039 --> 00:10:41,746
Cathy can help out more
with the twins.

180
00:10:41,807 --> 00:10:43,184
<font color="#808080">(CORRINE SIGHS)</font>

181
00:10:45,411 --> 00:10:47,789
People have
a way of believing...

182
00:10:47,813 --> 00:10:49,690
That nothing bad
can ever happen.

183
00:10:49,749 --> 00:10:51,285
And your father
was doing so well...

184
00:10:51,350 --> 00:10:53,330
At his job, so...

185
00:10:53,386 --> 00:10:55,992
We charged
against our future.

186
00:10:56,055 --> 00:10:58,399
What do you mean?

187
00:10:58,658 --> 00:11:00,137
Nothing here
is really ours.

188
00:11:00,192 --> 00:11:03,969
Not the furniture,
the cars, your toys...

189
00:11:04,030 --> 00:11:06,135
N-not even
this necklace.

190
00:11:06,732 --> 00:11:08,109
It's been four months...

191
00:11:08,167 --> 00:11:09,771
And I've been
holding them at bay...

192
00:11:09,835 --> 00:11:11,940
But the bank is going
to come and take it all away.

193
00:11:12,705 --> 00:11:13,979
Look, I know
it sounds scary...

194
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:16,350
But I've saved the best news
for last.

195
00:11:16,409 --> 00:11:18,685
My family is rich.

196
00:11:18,744 --> 00:11:21,748
Not middle-class rich,
but unbelievably wealthy...

197
00:11:21,814 --> 00:11:24,055
And they have one of the finest
homes in all of Virginia...

198
00:11:24,116 --> 00:11:24,924
With servants,

199
00:11:24,984 --> 00:11:27,726
and acres of land,
and their very own lake.

200
00:11:27,787 --> 00:11:29,227
Wait till we tell
everyone at school.

201
00:11:29,255 --> 00:11:30,996
We leave tonight.

202
00:11:31,057 --> 00:11:33,162
Tonight?

203
00:11:33,225 --> 00:11:34,761
It's our only choice.

204
00:11:34,827 --> 00:11:38,104
I know it's hard,
but I promise you...

205
00:11:38,130 --> 00:11:39,370
Whatever you leave behind...

206
00:11:39,398 --> 00:11:41,901
I'll buy you a thousand more
in Virginia.

207
00:11:41,967 --> 00:11:42,843
You won't miss a thing.

208
00:11:42,902 --> 00:11:44,939
Don't worry, mom.

209
00:11:45,004 --> 00:11:47,006
We're dollangangers.

210
00:11:47,073 --> 00:11:48,814
We'll be happy wherever.

211
00:11:48,874 --> 00:11:51,286
I knew I could count
on you, Christopher.

212
00:12:00,152 --> 00:12:01,256
And one more thing...

213
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:04,062
Our name
isn't really dollanganger.

214
00:12:04,123 --> 00:12:05,796
It's foxworth.

215
00:12:11,464 --> 00:12:13,034
<font color="#808080">(TRAIN RUMBLING OVER TRACKS)</font>

216
00:12:13,099 --> 00:12:14,908
<font color="#804040">CHRISTOPHER</font>:
I bet the house is huge.

217
00:12:14,967 --> 00:12:16,913
I mean, you could have
your own dance studio...

218
00:12:16,969 --> 00:12:18,414
With costumes
and a grand piano.

219
00:12:18,471 --> 00:12:20,815
I wouldn't even
hear you.

220
00:12:20,873 --> 00:12:23,444
You'll be out exploring
the woods and the lake.

221
00:12:23,509 --> 00:12:26,046
Way better
than any boring biology class.

222
00:12:26,112 --> 00:12:28,114
Ma'am?

223
00:12:28,180 --> 00:12:29,955
We'll reach your depot
in a few minutes.

224
00:12:30,015 --> 00:12:31,517
Thank you.

225
00:12:31,951 --> 00:12:33,362
You're sure
you wouldn't rather...

226
00:12:33,419 --> 00:12:35,092
Get off
in charlottesville?

227
00:12:35,154 --> 00:12:36,154
It's 3:00h A.M...

228
00:12:36,155 --> 00:12:37,463
In the middle
of nowhere.

229
00:12:37,523 --> 00:12:40,367
Oh, thank you.
We have someone meeting us.

230
00:12:41,026 --> 00:12:42,334
Just the children's bag.

231
00:12:42,394 --> 00:12:44,931
Someone will
pick up mine tomorrow.

232
00:12:46,065 --> 00:12:47,976
Thank you.

233
00:12:48,033 --> 00:12:49,808
Where are we going?

234
00:12:49,869 --> 00:12:51,473
Have a good night.

235
00:12:51,537 --> 00:12:53,346
Godspeed,
Mrs. Patterson.

236
00:13:07,229 --> 00:13:08,229
I thought you said...

237
00:13:08,254 --> 00:13:09,858
There was someone
meeting us.

238
00:13:11,056 --> 00:13:12,501
We should be there
before the sun breaks.

239
00:13:12,558 --> 00:13:14,003
It's a long walk.

240
00:13:14,393 --> 00:13:15,872
How long?

241
00:13:15,928 --> 00:13:17,134
I can't carry
the twins.

242
00:13:17,196 --> 00:13:18,231
Well, let them walk.

243
00:13:18,297 --> 00:13:20,800
The country air
will do them good.

244
00:13:31,577 --> 00:13:33,079
<font color="#804040">CARRIE</font>:
Where are we going?

245
00:13:33,145 --> 00:13:35,022
I want to go back home now!

246
00:13:35,080 --> 00:13:38,357
Just a little further,
and everything will be all right.

247
00:13:38,384 --> 00:13:40,057
You really think so?

248
00:13:40,119 --> 00:13:42,998
Yes. If that's
what mom said.

249
00:13:57,036 --> 00:13:58,913
This is
foxworth hall.

250
00:14:17,156 --> 00:14:20,069
Okay, Cory,
blow your nose, okay?

251
00:14:20,125 --> 00:14:21,866
Okay. Good. Good.

252
00:14:22,595 --> 00:14:24,472
Okay, Cathy,
button this button.

253
00:14:26,398 --> 00:14:28,878
<font color="#808080">(DOOR CREAKS OPEN)</font>

254
00:14:30,636 --> 00:14:32,445
