and lonely.

510
00:29:24,896 --> 00:29:29,811
And into all this came
my father's half-brother.

511
00:29:29,868 --> 00:29:33,145
His mother had recently died
and my family took him in.

512
00:29:33,204 --> 00:29:35,241
He was only
a few years older than me.

513
00:29:35,306 --> 00:29:40,187
But he was so handsome
and so kind, and, uh...

514
00:29:40,211 --> 00:29:41,781
So full of life.

515
00:29:41,813 --> 00:29:43,121
<font color="#808080">(SAD CHUCKLE)</font>

516
00:29:43,181 --> 00:29:45,923
My father treated him
like he was his own son...

517
00:29:45,984 --> 00:29:47,861
And I'd never met
anyone like him.

518
00:29:51,156 --> 00:29:52,156
<i><font color="#808080">(SIGHS)</font></i>

519
00:29:52,857 --> 00:29:55,269
You're talking about dad?

520
00:29:59,831 --> 00:30:02,107
We tried to keep
our feelings secret...

521
00:30:02,167 --> 00:30:03,544
Even from each other.

522
00:30:03,802 --> 00:30:05,304
I mean, we were
related by blood.

523
00:30:05,370 --> 00:30:06,974
He was my half-Uncle.

524
00:30:07,038 --> 00:30:08,244
And when we eloped...

525
00:30:08,306 --> 00:30:11,810
My family flew into a rage
and my father disinherited me

526
00:30:11,876 --> 00:30:12,876
and my mother said...

527
00:30:12,877 --> 00:30:15,357
That my children would be
born with hooved feet...

528
00:30:15,413 --> 00:30:17,051
And forked tails.

529
00:30:17,115 --> 00:30:19,493
She was wrong.

530
00:30:19,517 --> 00:30:21,087
God didn't punish me,
not with you.

531
00:30:21,152 --> 00:30:23,359
You are perfect.

532
00:30:23,421 --> 00:30:26,265
You have to believe it,
no matter what anyone says.

533
00:30:26,324 --> 00:30:27,530
I hope you
can understand...

534
00:30:27,592 --> 00:30:32,507
That love doesn't always come
when you want it.

535
00:30:32,530 --> 00:30:36,068
Sometimes it just happens,
against your will.

536
00:30:37,502 --> 00:30:40,847
I don't care what you did,
mom, or do.

537
00:30:42,240 --> 00:30:43,514
I'll always love you.

538
00:30:47,545 --> 00:30:50,048
Why did grandmother
let you come back?

539
00:30:50,348 --> 00:30:52,055
Because she's been
waiting 20 years...

540
00:30:52,116 --> 00:30:53,254
To say
"I told you so."

541
00:30:53,518 --> 00:30:55,464
Trust me, Cathy...

542
00:30:55,520 --> 00:30:58,399
I'm as much a captive
of this place as you are.

543
00:31:06,164 --> 00:31:07,370
Hey, cor'.

544
00:31:07,432 --> 00:31:08,911
That's a great...

545
00:31:08,967 --> 00:31:10,173
It's a snail.

546
00:31:10,235 --> 00:31:13,273
I can't wait to show it
to mama when she comes.

547
00:31:15,173 --> 00:31:16,173
If she comes.

548
00:31:16,174 --> 00:31:17,585
She's only missed
a few days.

549
00:31:17,642 --> 00:31:19,280
A week.

550
00:31:19,310 --> 00:31:20,516
I've made a calendar.

551
00:31:33,524 --> 00:31:35,504
You going to help out
with the garden or what?

552
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:37,062
We need water.

553
00:31:44,435 --> 00:31:47,143
Watch where you're going!

554
00:31:47,472 --> 00:31:49,383
Why are you
in such a hurry?

555
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:51,920
Sorry, I-i just had to
get some more water

556
00:31:51,943 --> 00:31:53,684
for Christopher
before the paint dries.

557
00:31:53,945 --> 00:31:55,322
The paint?

558
00:31:55,380 --> 00:31:57,053
We're building
a garden...

559
00:31:57,115 --> 00:32:00,153
In the attic so the twins
won't be so scared.

560
00:32:00,218 --> 00:32:01,526
Was this
your mother's idea?

561
00:32:03,087 --> 00:32:06,933
Hope you didn't inherit
her artistic abilities.

562
00:32:06,991 --> 00:32:11,064
The only real talent
corrine ever had was...

563
00:32:11,129 --> 00:32:13,166
For the opposite sex.

564
00:32:14,632 --> 00:32:17,943
I'm a dancer, actually.
Ballet.

565
00:32:18,002 --> 00:32:20,073
And Christopher's
a really good artist.

566
00:32:20,104 --> 00:32:21,208
He can paint anything.

567
00:32:21,272 --> 00:32:23,047
Has he ever
painted you?

568
00:32:24,676 --> 00:32:26,656
Has he asked you
to pose for him...

569
00:32:26,711 --> 00:32:29,089
With your clothes off?

570
00:32:29,147 --> 00:32:30,147
Come on, girl!

571
00:32:30,148 --> 00:32:31,252
Spit out the truth!

572
00:32:31,316 --> 00:32:33,728
I want to know what kind
of wickedness you're up to!

573
00:32:34,485 --> 00:32:35,657
Nothing.

574
00:32:36,254 --> 00:32:37,699
Nothing?

575
00:32:37,956 --> 00:32:38,991
Why are you trembling?

576
00:32:39,057 --> 00:32:42,231
Because you keep accusing us
of doing all these bad things

577
00:32:42,293 --> 00:32:44,295
and I don't even know
what you're talking about.

578
00:32:44,362 --> 00:32:48,504
Yeah, you don't know
what I'm talking about.

579
00:32:49,334 --> 00:32:51,371
Ask your brother!

580
00:32:51,436 --> 00:32:53,677
He'll know.

581
00:32:53,738 --> 00:32:55,046
By the time they're born...

582
00:32:55,106 --> 00:32:57,382
The male of the species...

583
00:32:57,442 --> 00:33:01,185
They know all about
wickedness and...

584
00:33:02,180 --> 00:33:03,682
Evil.

585
00:33:10,321 --> 00:33:12,562
Right. Now, make sure
that you take all of your toys.

586
00:33:12,623 --> 00:33:14,603
Check under the beds
to make sure.

587
00:33:14,659 --> 00:33:16,639
I don't want
any trace of you here.

588
00:33:16,728 --> 00:33:18,537
Why don't you take this?

589
00:33:21,766 --> 00:33:23,643
Why does this table
look polished?

590
00:33:23,701 --> 00:33:25,578
I wiped off
our fingerprints.

591
00:33:25,636 --> 00:33:28,617
The room can't look
like it's just been dusted!

592
00:33:28,673 --> 00:33:31,017
The maids are going to be here
in less than an hour.

593
00:33:31,442 --> 00:33:34,082
All right, never mind.
I'll take care of it.

594
00:33:34,145 --> 00:33:35,647
Uh...

595
00:33:37,348 --> 00:33:42,422
here are some real flowers
for your fake garden.

596
00:33:45,256 --> 00:33:46,564
Just go.

597
00:34:00,138 --> 00:34:01,617
"See Jane run.

598
00:34:01,672 --> 00:34:04,414
Run, Jane, run."

599
00:34:04,475 --> 00:34:06,182
Now you try.

600
00:34:06,244 --> 00:34:07,052
No!

601
00:34:07,111 --> 00:34:10,786
We've already read it
a gazillion times.

602
00:34:11,049 --> 00:34:13,051
<font color="#804040">CATHY</font>: If you guys
play nicely tonight...

603
00:34:13,117 --> 00:34:14,755
We can go on the roof
tomorrow morning.

604
00:34:14,819 --> 00:34:16,321
<font color="#804040">CORY</font>: I don't want
to go on the roof.

605
00:34:16,387 --> 00:34:18,458
Mom!

606
00:34:18,489 --> 00:34:20,594
We missed you so much!

607
00:34:21,059 --> 00:34:23,403
I'm sorry I've kept you
waiting so long, darlings.

608
00:34:23,461 --> 00:34:25,202
But here's some games...

609
00:34:25,263 --> 00:34:27,140
And the paints
you asked for, Cathy.

610
00:34:27,298 --> 00:34:28,402
Where have you been?

611
00:34:29,133 --> 00:34:31,773
I wanted
to come earlier, but...

612
00:34:31,836 --> 00:34:34,180
I've had to spend every moment
with my father.

613
00:34:34,238 --> 00:34:36,343
You have no idea
how hard it's been on me.

614
00:34:36,407 --> 00:34:37,681
Today, I finally
just had a chance...

615
00:34:37,742 --> 00:34:38,812
To go sailing on the lake.

616
00:34:39,077 --> 00:34:41,079
You went sailing?

617
00:34:41,145 --> 00:34:43,216
You got some great
color, mom.

618
00:34:44,248 --> 00:34:46,125
Can you stay for
the twins' bedtime?

619
00:34:46,184 --> 00:34:48,289
<font color="#808080">(TWINS CHEERING)</font>
Yeah! Stay! Stay!

620
00:34:48,352 --> 00:34:50,423
I have a movie date
with an old friend.

621
00:34:50,488 --> 00:34:51,489
She keeps
asking me out...

622
00:34:51,556 --> 00:34:52,591
And I can't
keep refusing.

623
00:34:52,657 --> 00:34:54,637
But I would much rather
be with you guys!

624
00:34:54,692 --> 00:34:58,139
Then why aren't you downstairs
telling your father about us?

625
00:34:58,196 --> 00:34:59,800
Well, Cathy, I have to time it
very carefully.

626
00:34:59,864 --> 00:35:00,706
I only just got back.

627
00:35:00,765 --> 00:35:02,836
It's been a month!

628
00:35:03,468 --> 00:35:05,379
And I'm sick
of being in here.

629
00:35:05,436 --> 00:35:07,882
The twins need
fresh air and sunshine.

630
00:35:08,139 --> 00:35:09,812
I want to go sailing!

631
00:35:09,874 --> 00:35:11,683
Stop picking
on mom, Cathy.

632
00:35:11,742 --> 00:35:13,449
I just want to know when.

633
00:35:13,511 --> 00:35:15,582
When are you going to tell
your father about us?

634
00:35:15,646 --> 00:35:17,353
When do we get to leave?

635
00:35:17,782 --> 00:35:18,783
Like I said...

636
00:35:18,816 --> 00:35:20,818
My father has just
finally accepted me back.

637
00:35:20,885 --> 00:35:23,661
Then why can't he accept us?

638
00:35:23,721 --> 00:35:26,702
Are we so terrible,
or stupid, or ugly...

639
00:35:26,757 --> 00:35:29,795
That he wouldn't want to meet
his own grandchildren?

640
00:35:32,530 --> 00:35:33,600
I can't.

641
00:35:36,200 --> 00:35:39,204
I can't tell him
about you, ever.

642
00:35:39,270 --> 00:35:41,807
My father forgave me
on one condition...

643
00:35:41,839 --> 00:35:44,513
That I didn't have any children
with your father.

644
00:35:50,148 --> 00:35:51,286
You know what?

645
00:35:51,349 --> 00:35:52,623
I'll cancel
my movie date...

646
00:35:52,683 --> 00:35:55,186
And I'll stay here
with you and the twins.

647
00:35:55,253 --> 00:35:56,698
It's okay, mom.

648
00:35:58,489 --> 00:35:59,559
You go.

649
00:36:01,592 --> 00:36:03,299
We'll be fine here.

650
00:36:20,711 --> 00:36:22,850
He could go
any day now.

651
00:36:22,914 --> 00:36:25,360
That's how
heart disease works.

652
00:36:25,416 --> 00:36:26,861
A blood clot
could break free...

653
00:36:26,884 --> 00:36:29,763
And find it's way
to his lungs or heart...

654
00:36:29,820 --> 00:36:30,924
Snuff him out
like a candle.

655
00:36:31,189 --> 00:36:33,635
With our luck,
grandfather will never die.

656
00:36:33,691 --> 00:36:34,965
We'll be stuck
up here forever.

657
00:36:35,226 --> 00:36:38,400
What's few more weeks?
A month, even?

658
00:36:38,462 --> 00:36:40,442
Pretty soon, we're going
to be worth millions.

659
00:36:40,498 --> 00:36:42,603
Mom already acts
like she is.

660
00:36:42,633 --> 00:36:43,509
Have you noticed...

661
00:36:43,568 --> 00:36:45,275
How she's always
in a new outfit?

662
00:36:45,336 --> 00:36:46,371
She's a foxworth.

663
00:36:46,437 --> 00:36:48,542
She has to fit in
around here.

664
00:36:48,606 --> 00:36:50,813
Cory's a cheater!

665
00:36:50,875 --> 00:36:52,946
I thought you guys were
playing hide-and-seek.

666
00:36:53,211 --> 00:36:53,746
We were!

667
00:36:53,811 --> 00:36:56,257
But I called and called
and he won't come out.

668
00:36:59,951 --> 00:37:01,259
Cory!

669
00:37:01,319 --> 00:37:03,265
Where are you?

670
00:37:08,292 --> 00:37:10,636
Christopher.
Over here.

671
00:37:27,745 --> 00:37:29,418
It's going to be okay.

672
00:37:29,981 --> 00:37:32,325
We just need to get him
warmed up.

673
00:37:49,600 --> 00:37:51,045
Cathy?

674
00:37:53,738 --> 00:37:56,014
I miss mama so much.

675
00:37:56,274 --> 00:37:58,811
Pretend I'm your mom.

676
00:37:58,876 --> 00:38:00,856
I love you so much.

677
00:38:00,911 --> 00:38:03,687
That's what makes
a real mother.

678
00:38:05,283 --> 00:38:06,694
<font color="#808080">(FOOTSTEPS)</font>

679
00:38:49,393 --> 00:38:52,033
Our first Christmas
without dad.

680
00:38:55,700 --> 00:38:57,611
Remember how he used
to take us sledding...

681
00:38:57,668 --> 00:38:59,375
Behind the flanagans"?

682
00:39:00,671 --> 00:39:02,878
He was always
running alongside us...

683
00:39:02,907 --> 00:39:05,046
Making sure
the twins were safe.

684
00:39:09,380 --> 00:39:11,417
One Christmas
up here won't matter.

685
00:39:12,016 --> 00:39:14,519
And we can make our own
presents for the twins.

686
00:39:14,585 --> 00:39:15,825
Say it's from Santa.

687
00:39:15,886 --> 00:39:17,888
We could make something
for grandmother, too.

688
00:39:17,955 --> 00:39:20,367
She does bring us
food every day.

689
00:39:20,758 --> 00:39:22,704
She got us that plant.

690
00:39:23,861 --> 00:39:25,863
She might even let us out.

691
00:39:30,134 --> 00:39:31,477
Hurry, Cathy!

692
00:39:31,535 --> 00:39:32,707
She's going to
be here.

693
00:39:32,770 --> 00:39:34,374
Careful.
I don't want it to rip.

694
00:39:34,438 --> 00:39:35,781
Christopher,
can I have the card?

695
00:39:35,840 --> 00:39:37,683
It has to be perfect.

696
00:39:47,551 --> 00:39:48,655
Grandmother?

697
00:40:23,053 --> 00:40:26,591
Cathy! Cathy!
Wake up. Santa came!

698
00:40:30,060 --> 00:40:31,562
This gift
is not from Santa.

699
00:40:31,629 --> 00:40:33,802
It's for Cory and Carrie
to play pretend house...

700
00:40:33,864 --> 00:40:34,864
Just like I did.

701
00:40:34,865 --> 00:40:36,640
And all the doors and windows
really work...

702
00:40:36,700 --> 00:40:37,700
And the locks.

703
00:40:41,071 --> 00:40:43,210
I knew that color
would look perfect on you.

704
00:40:43,707 --> 00:40:45,880
You look just like your father
when I first met him.

705
00:40:46,444 --> 00:40:47,752
You think so?

706
00:40:53,951 --> 00:40:55,123
I got this
sent from Paris.

707
00:40:55,186 --> 00:40:57,063
It's hand-embroidered.

708
00:40:57,121 --> 00:40:58,623
Don't you like it?

709
00:40:58,689 --> 00:41:00,828
Yes.

710
00:41:01,592 --> 00:41:03,799
I just don't know
where I'd wear it.

711
00:41:04,895 --> 00:41:06,875
Well, I know it's not
a perfect Christmas...

712
00:41:06,931 --> 00:41:09,468
But I still have
one more trick up my sleeve.

713
00:41:12,236 --> 00:41:14,238
A window
to the outside world.

714
00:41:14,805 --> 00:41:16,512
My father
gave it to me.

715
00:41:16,574 --> 00:41:17,484
But that's not all.

716
00:41:17,541 --> 00:41:19,612
Bart, Mr. winslow,
he says that my father...

717
00:41:19,643 --> 00:41:21,179
Has an even bigger
surprise for me.

718
00:41:21,245 --> 00:41:22,690
Who's Mr. winslow?

719
00:41:22,746 --> 00:41:23,918
He's my father's attorney.

720
00:41:23,981 --> 00:41:25,141
He says it's only a matter...

721
00:41:25,149 --> 00:41:27,527
Of drawing up
the new paperwork, but...

722
00:41:27,585 --> 00:41:29,622
I'm going to
inherit everything.

723
00:41:29,687 --> 00:41:31,633
<font color="#808080">(SQUEALS AND LAUGHS)</font>

724
00:41:34,024 --> 00:41:35,196
I knew you could do it, mom.

725
00:41:35,259 --> 00:41:36,829
He's throwing me
a party tonight...

726
00:41:36,894 --> 00:41:38,771
With champagne
and a live orchestra...

727
00:41:38,829 --> 00:41:39,671
And anyone who's anyone...

728
00:41:39,730 --> 00:41:41,141
- in Virginia.
- Can we come?

729
00:41:42,800 --> 00:41:43,835
Please?

730
00:41:43,901 --> 00:41:46,211
We'll hide somewhere
and we'll be quiet...

731
00:41:46,270 --> 00:41:48,580
And no one will hear us
or see us, I swear.

732
00:41:48,639 --> 00:41:49,811
I think it's too risky.

733
00:41:49,874 --> 00:41:52,821
I mean, after putting
in all this time...

734
00:41:52,877 --> 00:41:55,187
We haven't seen
other people in so long.

735
00:41:56,780 --> 00:41:59,056
It's the only thing
I really want.

736
00:41:59,083 --> 00:42:00,994
Don't you care
if I'm happy?

737
00:42:01,051 --> 00:42:02,121
Cathy, quit it.

738
00:42:02,186 --> 00:42:03,187
You think she's happy...

739
00:42:03,254 --> 00:42:04,733
Knowing her kids
are locked up in an attic?

740
00:42:04,788 --> 00:42:05,858
<i><font color="#808080">(SIGHS)</font></i>

741
00:42:05,923 --> 00:42:07,596
It's okay, Christopher.

742
00:42:08,692 --> 00:42:09,796
You can come.

743
00:42:09,860 --> 00:42:11,533
You can both come.

744
00:42:12,530 --> 00:42:13,873
After the twins
are asleep.

745
00:42:13,931 --> 00:42:16,935
I feel like, for the first time
since your father died...

746
00:42:17,001 --> 00:42:19,880
Things are finally
looking up for us.

747
00:42:25,009 --> 00:42:27,819
This is where I used to hide
and watch my parents' parties.

748
00:42:27,878 --> 00:42:29,186
Just remember
your promise, okay?

749
00:42:29,246 --> 00:42:30,554
Be quiet as mice.

750
00:42:30,581 --> 00:42:31,581
And after dinner...

751
00:42:31,582 --> 00:42:32,993
Go straight back
to our room.

752
00:42:33,050 --> 00:42:34,654
Yes.

753
00:42:43,060 --> 00:42:46,200
<font color="#808080">(BAND PLAYS CHRISTMAS MUSIC AS GUESTS BANTER)</font>

754
00:42:56,674 --> 00:42:57,982
<font color="#808080">(SIGHING)</font>

755
00:42:58,042 --> 00:43:00,147
The house hasn't been
so lively in years.

756
00:43:00,210 --> 00:43:01,951
And all this
because of you.

757
00:43:02,012 --> 00:43:03,184
That's what worries me.

758
00:43:03,247 --> 00:43:04,527
I hope I don't
disappoint anyone.

759
00:43:04,615 --> 00:43:07,926
Oh, no, miss foxworth,
you're as lovely as ever.

760
00:43:07,985 --> 00:43:09,726
Thank you, Sarah.

761
00:43:14,024 --> 00:43:15,594
That dress...

762
00:43:15,659 --> 00:43:18,765
Most women would be
too modest to wear it.

763
00:43:19,797 --> 00:43:21,299
I know you don't
approve of this party...

764
00:43:21,365 --> 00:43:22,365
But try to have fun...

765
00:43:22,366 --> 00:43:23,674
For father's sake.

766
00:43:23,734 --> 00:43:27,705
Your father's well-being
