01:16:22,945 --> 01:16:26,051
<font color="#808080">(DOOR OPENS)</font>

1270
01:16:26,248 --> 01:16:29,161
Cory doesn't feel so good.

1271
01:16:43,732 --> 01:16:45,643
He's been
vomiting for hours.

1272
01:16:46,001 --> 01:16:47,378
I think it might be
food poisoning.

1273
01:16:47,636 --> 01:16:49,343
He needs to go
to the hospital.

1274
01:16:52,808 --> 01:16:54,981
Why are you just
standing there?

1275
01:16:55,310 --> 01:16:57,916
Don't you care
what happens to him?

1276
01:16:58,981 --> 01:17:01,689
Have you forgotten
that you're his mother?

1277
01:17:01,750 --> 01:17:03,627
You.

1278
01:17:03,685 --> 01:17:05,687
It's always you.

1279
01:17:10,359 --> 01:17:11,667
Cathy, stop!

1280
01:17:11,727 --> 01:17:13,206
You think you can do
anything you want...

1281
01:17:13,261 --> 01:17:14,865
And people will believe you.

1282
01:17:14,930 --> 01:17:16,841
They'll learn the truth someday.

1283
01:17:16,898 --> 01:17:19,902
When your husband learns
you have four children...

1284
01:17:19,968 --> 01:17:22,073
Locked away in an attic...

1285
01:17:22,137 --> 01:17:24,640
See how "perfect"
he thinks you really are.

1286
01:17:24,706 --> 01:17:26,686
And your father, too.

1287
01:17:26,742 --> 01:17:29,313
You won't inherit
one damned penny...

1288
01:17:29,378 --> 01:17:30,880
And I'll be glad!

1289
01:17:32,247 --> 01:17:34,386
The girl is right, corrine.

1290
01:17:34,650 --> 01:17:36,823
That child should go
to the hospital.

1291
01:18:02,077 --> 01:18:03,147
<font color="#808080">(FLOOR CREAKING)</font>

1292
01:18:03,211 --> 01:18:05,213
<font color="#808080">(LOCK TURNING)</font>

1293
01:18:14,890 --> 01:18:16,801
I drove Cory to the hospital.

1294
01:18:17,693 --> 01:18:18,831
How is he?

1295
01:18:21,129 --> 01:18:23,109
Cory had pneumonia.

1296
01:18:23,131 --> 01:18:26,408
The doctors did
all they could, but...

1297
01:18:26,902 --> 01:18:29,348
It was too late.

1298
01:18:37,012 --> 01:18:38,719
Will there be
a funeral?

1299
01:18:39,247 --> 01:18:41,318
He's already been buried.

1300
01:18:47,289 --> 01:18:50,065
<font color="#808080">(STARTS CRYING)</font>

1301
01:18:59,468 --> 01:19:03,883
<font color="#808080">(CARRIE CRYING)</font>

1302
01:19:08,176 --> 01:19:09,849
I'm sorry.

1303
01:19:19,855 --> 01:19:21,266
<font color="#804040">CATHY</font>:
Carrie?

1304
01:19:24,526 --> 01:19:26,369
Cathy.

1305
01:19:26,428 --> 01:19:28,101
Just let her be.

1306
01:19:33,935 --> 01:19:35,881
We need to run away.

1307
01:19:35,937 --> 01:19:38,417
Or else we're all
going to die like Cory.

1308
01:19:38,807 --> 01:19:39,979
Do we have
enough money?

1309
01:19:40,041 --> 01:19:40,849
We'll go tonight.

1310
01:19:40,909 --> 01:19:43,116
Take everything we can.
Money, jewelry.

1311
01:19:43,779 --> 01:19:44,779
Everything.

1312
01:20:17,145 --> 01:20:19,421
<font color="#808080">(VOICE BREAKING)</font>
She's not coming back.

1313
01:20:20,582 --> 01:20:21,583
Is she?

1314
01:20:23,852 --> 01:20:25,559
She's dead to us now.

1315
01:20:31,860 --> 01:20:33,134
When do we tell her?

1316
01:20:33,195 --> 01:20:34,572
After breakfast.

1317
01:20:34,830 --> 01:20:37,140
I don't want her
getting scared.

1318
01:20:37,199 --> 01:20:38,371
More than she has to be.

1319
01:20:40,869 --> 01:20:42,507
So we just walk right
out the front door?

1320
01:20:42,571 --> 01:20:43,914
We wait till dinner...

1321
01:20:43,972 --> 01:20:45,042
When all the servants
and family...

1322
01:20:45,106 --> 01:20:46,427
Are in the kitchen
or dining room.

1323
01:20:46,474 --> 01:20:47,509
So Carrie and I will
go to the fence...

1324
01:20:47,542 --> 01:20:48,919
And you'll go to the shed...

1325
01:20:48,977 --> 01:20:50,149
So you can turn off
the electricity?

1326
01:20:50,212 --> 01:20:51,412
Then we catch up
by the lake...

1327
01:20:51,446 --> 01:20:53,255
And head to the depot
for the evening train.

1328
01:20:54,082 --> 01:20:55,527
And by the time
grandmother comes in...

1329
01:20:55,584 --> 01:20:56,744
With our breakfast
tomorrow...

1330
01:20:56,852 --> 01:20:58,854
We'll be halfway
to Florida.

1331
01:21:01,456 --> 01:21:04,130
I was thinking,
I can sell my ring.

1332
01:21:06,595 --> 01:21:07,595
It's okay.

1333
01:21:07,629 --> 01:21:09,609
It's what
dad would have wanted.

1334
01:21:09,865 --> 01:21:11,071
You're keeping that ring.

1335
01:21:11,132 --> 01:21:13,305
Forever.

1336
01:21:13,368 --> 01:21:15,871
<font color="#808080">(STARTS COUGHING)</font>

1337
01:21:42,264 --> 01:21:44,471
I'm telling you,
I did hear someone.

1338
01:21:44,532 --> 01:21:46,534
Must be those mice.
They make an awful racket.

1339
01:21:46,601 --> 01:21:48,308
You can hear them
all the way up in the attic.

1340
01:21:48,370 --> 01:21:50,680
Mrs. foxworth carries
enough poison up there...

1341
01:21:50,939 --> 01:21:53,078
To kill
a German army of them.

1342
01:21:53,141 --> 01:21:55,485
Do you think miss corrine
will sell the place?

1343
01:21:55,543 --> 01:21:57,921
I doubt she'll be
making any hasty decisions.

1344
01:21:57,946 --> 01:21:59,983
Hasty? It's been
seven months

1345
01:22:00,048 --> 01:22:01,356
since Mr. foxworth died.

1346
01:22:01,416 --> 01:22:03,020
Well, never mind that.

1347
01:22:03,084 --> 01:22:05,928
All you maids will be
losing your job soon enough...

1348
01:22:05,987 --> 01:22:08,194
If you don't
mind the silver.

1349
01:22:11,426 --> 01:22:14,168
<font color="#808080">(FOOTFALLS RECEDING)</font>

1350
01:22:17,666 --> 01:22:19,373
Carrie, you got
to eat something.

1351
01:22:19,434 --> 01:22:21,937
You have to be strong,
for later.

1352
01:22:22,003 --> 01:22:23,710
No. Don't feel well.

1353
01:22:23,972 --> 01:22:26,350
I have to
take care of Mickey.

1354
01:22:28,310 --> 01:22:29,448
Where'd you get that?

1355
01:22:30,178 --> 01:22:31,282
I saved it for Cory...

1356
01:22:31,346 --> 01:22:34,350
For when he came back
from the hospital.

1357
01:22:54,102 --> 01:22:56,139
<font color="#808080">(COUGHING QUIETLY)</font>

1358
01:23:13,121 --> 01:23:16,125
Cathy, we need to
leave right now.

1359
01:23:17,125 --> 01:23:19,230
<font color="#808080">(SNIFFLING)</font>

1360
01:23:19,327 --> 01:23:21,398
It's Mickey.

1361
01:23:22,464 --> 01:23:24,444
Carrie gave him
one of Cory's donuts

1362
01:23:24,499 --> 01:23:26,445
and he just started
whimpering all of a sudden...

1363
01:23:26,501 --> 01:23:29,482
no. No.
That can't be right.

1364
01:23:29,537 --> 01:23:30,743
What?

1365
01:23:31,006 --> 01:23:32,747
The powdered sugar
on the donuts...

1366
01:23:33,008 --> 01:23:34,612
I think
there was poison in it.

1367
01:23:34,676 --> 01:23:36,019
That's why we're sick.

1368
01:23:36,044 --> 01:23:38,024
Are you saying that
our grandmother...

1369
01:23:38,046 --> 01:23:39,150
Tried to kill us?

1370
01:23:41,182 --> 01:23:43,423
You have a key.

1371
01:23:43,451 --> 01:23:45,021
<font color="#808080">(DOOR BANGS SHUT)</font>

1372
01:23:45,086 --> 01:23:47,498
Now give it to me.

1373
01:23:50,358 --> 01:23:52,167
No.

1374
01:23:52,193 --> 01:23:54,366
Give it to me
this instant!

1375
01:23:55,363 --> 01:23:57,570
<font color="#808080">(WRACKED WITH COUGHING)</font>

1376
01:23:57,599 --> 01:23:58,737
Seed of the devil!

1377
01:24:01,770 --> 01:24:04,444
Give me that!

1378
01:24:04,506 --> 01:24:06,577
You're never going
to leave this room!

1379
01:24:08,309 --> 01:24:10,516
<font color="#808080">(SCOFFING)</font>
You're some to hit me?

1380
01:24:11,546 --> 01:24:13,583
You're going to whip me?

1381
01:24:13,648 --> 01:24:15,059
Come on!

1382
01:24:15,116 --> 01:24:17,255
Come on. Do it.

1383
01:24:18,186 --> 01:24:20,257
<font color="#808080">(SNICKERING)</font>

1384
01:24:21,589 --> 01:24:23,762
Beautiful, prideful...

1385
01:24:23,825 --> 01:24:24,825
And weak!

1386
01:24:25,060 --> 01:24:26,232
Just like your mother.

1387
01:24:26,294 --> 01:24:27,739
That's not true.

1388
01:24:27,796 --> 01:24:29,469
You were never
meant to be born.

1389
01:24:30,265 --> 01:24:32,677
You're a stain
on the foxworth name!

1390
01:24:32,734 --> 01:24:35,340
On the name
of the lord himself.

1391
01:24:35,403 --> 01:24:37,815
Now, if you
give me that key...

1392
01:24:38,073 --> 01:24:40,781
I may show you
a little mercy.

1393
01:24:44,479 --> 01:24:45,753
Christopher...

1394
01:24:45,780 --> 01:24:46,780
Come on!

1395
01:24:49,350 --> 01:24:51,296
Christopher...

1396
01:24:51,352 --> 01:24:52,695
<font color="#808080">(GASPS)</font>
Let go!

1397
01:24:52,754 --> 01:24:54,290
Cathy, go to the attic!

1398
01:24:54,355 --> 01:24:55,834
No! Give me that!

1399
01:24:57,459 --> 01:25:00,497
Come back here!
Come back here!

1400
01:25:00,762 --> 01:25:02,764
Carrie, please!

1401
01:25:02,797 --> 01:25:05,573
<font color="#808080">(CARRIE GASPING)</font>

1402
01:25:05,633 --> 01:25:07,442
Cathy!

1403
01:25:07,502 --> 01:25:09,243
<font color="#808080">(BANGS DOOR SHUT)</font>

1404
01:25:10,271 --> 01:25:11,511
Why did you do that?

1405
01:25:12,574 --> 01:25:14,713
Don't close the door.

1406
01:25:14,776 --> 01:25:17,848
I need for the door
to be open!

1407
01:25:20,515 --> 01:25:22,188
No. Not the door.

1408
01:25:22,250 --> 01:25:23,524
Don't turn off
the light.

1409
01:25:23,585 --> 01:25:25,531
Open the door!
Turn on the light!

1410
01:25:25,587 --> 01:25:28,727
I need the door
to be open!

1411
01:25:28,790 --> 01:25:31,134
What are you doing?

1412
01:25:31,159 --> 01:25:34,572
No! No! Open the door!

1413
01:25:35,130 --> 01:25:36,438
<font color="#808080">(WEEPING)</font>
No!

1414
01:25:36,498 --> 01:25:37,704
What are you doing?

1415
01:25:40,235 --> 01:25:41,543
Like you said...

1416
01:25:41,603 --> 01:25:43,742
God sees everything.

1417
01:25:43,805 --> 01:25:46,513
He'll punish you
for what you did to us.

1418
01:25:46,574 --> 01:25:48,554
To Cory.

1419
01:25:49,611 --> 01:25:51,750
It wasn't me!

1420
01:25:51,813 --> 01:25:55,852
It was your mother
who poisoned you, not me!

1421
01:25:58,753 --> 01:26:00,596
It doesn't
matter anymore.

1422
01:26:00,655 --> 01:26:02,635
<font color="#808080">(GRANDMOTHER SOBBING)</font>

1423
01:26:02,690 --> 01:26:04,670
Where are you going?

1424
01:26:04,726 --> 01:26:06,433
Don't go!

1425
01:26:06,461 --> 01:26:07,667
Don't leave me!

1426
01:26:07,729 --> 01:26:10,869
Help! Help!

1427
01:26:10,932 --> 01:26:12,775
Help!

1428
01:26:14,435 --> 01:26:16,745
<font color="#808080">(CHRISTOPHER COUGHING)</font>

1429
01:26:26,814 --> 01:26:28,919
Cathy, we have to go.

1430
01:26:29,184 --> 01:26:30,720
Be right there.

1431
01:26:32,820 --> 01:26:34,322
<font color="#808080">(CHALK CLATTERS)</font>

1432
01:26:51,906 --> 01:26:52,907
<font color="#808080">(ROPE CREAKING)</font>

1433
01:26:57,345 --> 01:26:58,345
<font color="#808080">(GASPING)</font>

1434
01:26:58,346 --> 01:27:00,656
<font color="#808080">(THUD)</font>

1435
01:27:00,715 --> 01:27:01,887
Are you okay?

1436
01:27:03,384 --> 01:27:04,385
Come on.

1437
01:27:12,360 --> 01:27:14,772
I'll cut the electricity
and meet you at the lake.

1438
01:27:14,829 --> 01:27:15,830
No! No!

1439
01:27:15,897 --> 01:27:17,706
We're not
going without you.

1440
01:27:18,733 --> 01:27:20,735
Hurry!
We have to make this train.

1441
01:27:20,802 --> 01:27:21,906
Stop!

1442
01:27:21,970 --> 01:27:23,881
Stop, if you know
what's good for you!

1443
01:27:27,375 --> 01:27:29,377
Please...

1444
01:27:31,679 --> 01:27:33,681
We're corrine's children.

1445
01:27:37,318 --> 01:27:38,388
My God.

1446
01:27:41,556 --> 01:27:42,556
Go.

1447
01:27:42,624 --> 01:27:43,728
Before I'm sent
after you!

1448
01:27:43,791 --> 01:27:45,031
I'll cut the power
on the fence.

1449
01:27:45,260 --> 01:27:46,739
Go!

1450
01:27:52,634 --> 01:27:54,807
<font color="#808080">(CHUGGING)</font>

1451
01:28:12,720 --> 01:28:16,031
We never have to see
that place again, cath.

1452
01:28:17,292 --> 01:28:18,771
It's all over.

1453
01:28:19,627 --> 01:28:22,506
<font color="#804040">CATHY</font>: And for the first
time in a long time...

1454
01:28:22,563 --> 01:28:24,668
We felt alive...

1455
01:28:24,732 --> 01:28:25,836
Free.

1456
01:28:25,900 --> 01:28:28,005
We had everything ahead of us.

1457
01:28:30,038 --> 01:28:33,884
But someday,
we'd see mom again.

1458
01:28:33,941 --> 01:28:36,547
And we'd look her
straight in the eye...

1459
01:28:37,345 --> 01:28:39,689
The children she once loved...

1460
01:28:40,348 --> 01:28:42,692
And all our shame
and hopelessness...

1461
01:28:42,750 --> 01:28:44,923
Would become hers.

1462
01:28:50,992 --> 01:28:57,705
<i>"U?"</i>

